<br>
The Catholic Church is based on 2 perogatives<br>
<br>
1) Pastoral Ministry - that is, taking care of its members and attending to their needs, both physical and spiritual<br>
<br>
2)  Maintaining its authority- in order to continue to exist and carry out function no.1<br>
<br>
So, the Catholic Church, in all of its &quot;obfuscating&quot; theories and teaching, (I would have to agree with you, I think), is caught in a paradox.  Will it cease to give sacraments and pastoral care and comfort to the woman who violates Catholic policy and takes birth-control?  No, probably not.  It will continue to administer to her needs and love her just the same, even at risk to its own authority.  <br>
<br>
Despite this paradox and dilemma, it continues to be the largest and most powerful religious organization in the world, providing comfort and meaning for millions.  <br>
<br>
My point is, even the most complicated and seemingly EXCLUSIVE organizations can be the most successful, even if their theology confuses the hell out of you.  <br>
<br>
Wyndigo<br>
