What events cannot be explianed? there is two very large grooves melted into the rock in a pyramid in south america leading to what can almost be described as an alter, possibly launch pad, the entire things is over 100' and the top peice is melted tooo. no volcanoes near, and what the hell could melt something like that into sheer rock in such a way?<br>
<br>
we are all looking for faith, wether we want to admit it or not. Some find faith in logical science, but that is flawed too whereas infinity exists between every number and peice of a number there is. and some continue to argue that science is absolute law even though it is based on a flawed principle and theory.<br>
i find my faith in god or the beuaty and incomprehensiveness of nature, where can a universe based upon principles of entropy produce a butterfly or my son. Noone knows the answers, we must find our own within ourselves.<br>
